                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_fæsm" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fæsm</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fans</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шерсть осенней стрижки</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>autumn shearing wool</q></tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>fæsmyn</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>из шерсти</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>of wool</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>шерстяной</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>woollen</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сукно (домотканное, осетинское)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>broadcloth (homespun, Ossetic)</q></tr></sense></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>tyn fæsmæj kænync, fīst næ bæzzy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сукно делают из шерсти осенней стрижки, шерсть весенней стрижки не годится</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>broadcloth is made from autumn shearing wool, spring shearing wool is no good</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>tyn fæsmæj kænync, fīst næ bæzzy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сукно делают из шерсти осенней стрижки, шерсть весенней стрижки не годится</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>broadcloth is made from autumn shearing wool, spring shearing wool is no good</q></tr></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*paš-man-</w></mentioned>; заключает тот же корень, что %ifas-yn%i ‘чесать шерсть’. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>pašm</w> <gloss><q>шерсть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pām, pōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>pam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>pōm</w> <gloss><q>шерсть овечья</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pakš-man-</w> <gloss><q>волосы, шерсть козули</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>fahs</w> <gloss><q>хохол</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πέκoς, πόκος</w> <gloss><q>овечья шерсть</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>руно</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Остальное см. под <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fasyn"/>. Дигорская форма %ifans%i — вторичная, ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_casm"/> | %icans%i ‘петля’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sasm"/> | %isans%i ‘клей’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘год’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæzmyn"/> | %ifænzun%i ‘подражать’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>361 прим., 379</biblScope></bibl>). Термины, связанные с шерстью и ее обработкой в осетинском, — иранского происхождения. Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр. 333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 333</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/> <w>*paš-man-</w></mentioned>; it has the same root as %ifas-yn%i ‘comb wool’. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>pašm</w> <gloss><q>wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>pām, pōm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/> <w>pam</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/> <w>pām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>pōm</w> <gloss><q>sheep wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>pakš-man-</w> <gloss><q>roe hair, roe wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/> <w>fahs</w> <gloss><q>crest</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>πέκoς, πόκος</w> <gloss><q>sheep wool</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/> <gloss><q>fleece</q></gloss></mentioned>, . See the rest under <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fasyn"/>. The Digor form %ifans%i is secondary, cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_casm"/> | %icans%i ‘loop’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sasm"/> | %isans%i ‘glue’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘year’, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæzmyn"/> | %ifænzun%i ‘imitate’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>361 footnote, 379</biblScope></bibl>). The terms associated with wool and its processing in Ossetic are of Iranian origin. Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_q0yn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Miller,_IF_21"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">стр. 333</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">p. 333</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 237</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>